[[ja:夏祭り]]

{{Otheruses}} {{Unreferenced|date=August 2014}} {{nihongo|Natsumatsuri|夏祭り}} refers to the general term for {{ill|summer festivals|ja|夏祭り}} held in {{ill|Japan|ja|日本}}. These festivals are typically held from early July to late August, although festivals held in September that correspond to the {{ill|lunisolar calendar|ja|旧暦}}'s seventh month are often treated as summer festivals<ref>Examples include Kimata Town Fireworks Festival and Arima Town Bon Dance.</ref>.
== Overview == Many of Japan's summer festivals are rooted in events such as {{ill|Obon|ja|盂蘭盆会}} (盂蘭盆会), {{ill|Tanabata|ja|七夕}}, and {{ill|Gion Matsuri|ja|祇園祭}}, or related rituals. As such, these festivals align with the sixth and seventh months of the old lunisolar calendar. In rural areas, these events often originated as part of relieving labor fatigue from summer farming activities. In urban areas, they are believed to stem from pre-{{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}} traditions of warding off summer epidemics and honoring the dead.
However, modernization has caused significant transformations in these festivals, and their origins are often not recognized. Summer festivals are now largely regarded as vibrant and festive events rather than solemn ones. Furthermore, many festivals lack origins before the Edo period, having been introduced in the modern era or modeled after traditional festivals from other regions.
Especially around the {{ill|Obon|ja|盂蘭盆会}} season in August, summer festivals are often associated with homecoming, creating opportunities for emotional reunions with loved ones{{Citation needed|date=October 2014}}.
In port towns, variations rich in local flavor, such as "Minato Matsuri" (harbor festivals), are common. Many {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} festivals also take place during this period.
== Events Held at Summer Festivals == * {{ill|Obon#Bon_Odori|lt=Bon Dance|ja|盆踊り}} * {{ill|Parades|ja|パレード}} * {{ill|Fireworks|ja|花火大会}} * {{ill|Yatai|ja|屋台}} (food stalls, often at {{ill|Ennichi|ja|縁日}}) * {{ill|Floats|ja|山車}} and {{ill|Festival music|ja|祭囃子}} * Events using temporary stages: ** Song shows ** Character shows (often featuring {{ill|Anime|ja|アニメ}}, {{ill|Super Sentai|ja|戦隊シリーズ}}, or {{ill|Local hero (Japan)|ja|ローカルヒーロー}}) ** {{ill|Magic (illusion)|ja|奇術}} shows ** {{ill|Karaoke|ja|カラオケ}} competitions
== Representative Summer Festivals in Japan == [[File:Aomori Nebuta Festival Float August 2006.jpg|thumb|180px|{{ill|Aomori Nebuta Festival|ja|青森ねぶた祭}}]] [[File:Sendai Tanabata Festival 2010.jpg|thumb|180px|{{ill|Sendai Tanabata Festival|ja|仙台七夕まつり}}]] [[File:Tomioka hachimangu10.jpg|thumb|180px|{{ill|Fukagawa Matsuri|ja|深川祭}}]] [[File:Gion Matsuri 2017-5.jpg|thumb|180px|{{ill|Gion Matsuri|ja|祇園祭}}]] [[File:Awa-odori 2008 Tokushima.jpg|thumb|180px|{{ill|Awa Odori|ja|阿波踊り}}]] * {{ill|Hokkaido|ja|北海道}} ** {{ill|Ubagami Daijingu Togyo Festival|ja|姥神大神宮渡御祭}} ** {{ill|Hakodate Port Festival|ja|函館港まつり}} – Features dances like the {{ill|Squid Dance|ja|いか踊り}}. * {{ill|Aomori Prefecture|ja|青森県}} ** {{ill|Aomori Nebuta Festival|ja|青森ねぶた祭}} – One of the {{ill|Three Great Festivals of Tohoku|ja|東北三大祭り}}. ** {{ill|Hirosaki Neputa Festival|ja|弘前ねぷたまつり}} * {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県}} ** {{ill|Sendai Tanabata Festival|ja|仙台七夕まつり}} – One of the Three Great Festivals of Tohoku. * {{ill|Akita Prefecture|ja|秋田県}} ** {{ill|Kanto Festival|ja|秋田竿燈まつり}} – One of the Three Great Festivals of Tohoku. * {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県}} ** {{ill|Fukushima Waraji Festival|ja|福島わらじまつり}} * {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県}} ** {{ill|Kiryu Yagibushi Festival|ja|桐生八木節まつり}} * {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都}} ** {{ill|Fukagawa Matsuri|ja|深川祭}} – One of the {{ill|Three Great Festivals of Edo|ja|江戸三大祭り}}. * {{ill|Ishikawa Prefecture|ja|石川県}} ** {{ill|Iida-machi Toro-yama Festival|ja|飯田町燈籠山祭り}} * {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県}} ** {{ill|Gujo Odori|ja|郡上踊り}} * {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}} ** {{ill|Owari Tsushima Tennō Festival|ja|尾張津島天王祭}} – One of the {{ill|Three Great River Festivals of Japan|ja|日本三大川祭}}. * {{ill|Kyoto Prefecture|ja|京都府}} ** {{ill|Gion Matsuri|ja|祇園祭}} – One of the {{ill|Three Great Festivals of Japan|ja|日本三大祭り}}. * {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府}} ** {{ill|Tenjin Matsuri|ja|天神祭}} – Part of the Three Great Festivals of Japan and the {{ill|Three Great Summer Festivals of Osaka|ja|大阪三大夏祭り}}. * {{ill|Hyogo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県}} ** {{ill|Yumura Onsen (Hyogo)|lt=Yumura Onsen (Hyogo)|lt=Yumura Onsen Fire Festival|ja|湯村温泉 (兵庫県)#イベント|ja|湯村温泉 (兵庫県)#イベント|ja|湯村温泉 (兵庫県)#イベント}} * {{ill|Tottori Prefecture|ja|鳥取県}} ** {{ill|Tottori Shan-Shan Festival|ja|鳥取しゃんしゃん祭}} * {{ill|Tokushima Prefecture|ja|徳島県}} ** {{ill|Awa Odori|ja|阿波踊り}} – Its {{ill|Tokushima City Awa Odori|ja|徳島市阿波おどり}} is one of the {{ill|Three Great Festivals of Shikoku|ja|四国三大祭り}}. * {{ill|Kochi Prefecture|ja|高知県}} ** {{ill|Yosakoi Festival|ja|よさこい祭り}} – One of the Three Great Festivals of Shikoku. * {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}} ** {{ill|Hakata Gion Yamakasa|ja|博多祇園山笠}} * {{ill|Kumamoto Prefecture|ja|熊本県}} ** {{ill|Yamaga Lantern Festival|ja|山鹿灯籠まつり}} * {{ill|Miyazaki Prefecture|ja|宮崎県}} ** {{ill|Miyakonojo Rokugatsudo Okage Festival|ja|都城六月灯おかげ祭り}}
== Summer Festivals Outside Japan == * {{ill|Sabantuy|ja|サバントゥイ}} – A summer festival held along the middle reaches of the {{ill|Volga River|ja|ヴォルガ川}} in {{ill|Russia|ja|ロシア}}.
